  "title": "NDT Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></p><p>· Ensure timely generation and issuance of\nNDT report on daily basis.</p><p>· The inspector/team lead / engineer will\nperform inspections applying various NDT techniques in accordance with\napplicable specific code, procedure, and or written criteria.</p><p>To be successful in this position, you must\nhave the ability to demonstrate or possess:</p><p>· Minimum 3 years of experience in UT, MT,\nPT, ET, RT and RI.</p><p>· Must be a PCN Level 2 or ISO Level II in\nthe above NDT methods.</p><p>· Familiar with codes and standards.</p><p>· Candidate must be flexible and responsive\nwhen call for assignments and willing to work after hours and weekends when\nnecessary.</p><p>· Maintain a professionalism and competence\nat work</p><p>· Share in our purpose – to serve others,\nto pursue excellence, and to grow profitably,</p><p>· Employee will work as a team lead /\nmember of local call out crews performing UT, MT, PT, ET, RT and RI.</p>",
